C130 Senior Engineer in the UAE
Aeropeople
-
United Kingdom
Temporary
Able to control all maintenance activities of first and second line of the C130 platform with the highest level of safety.
Detailed qualifications/experience/knowledge/skills:
Qualified and experienced Licensed Aircraft Engineer, for this 12 month minimum contract
7+years' experience in C-130 Aircraft Maintenance.
Preferable with A&C; and Avionics specialization on the type.
knowledgeabie of FAA regulations.
Able to plan, monitor and control manpower requirements needed for aircraft maintenance activities within base or line maintenance on day to day basis, and able to ensure strict administrative control of aircraft technicians.
Able to control and provide guidance to subordinate staff during troubleshooting aircraft defects.
Should have proven supervisory skills in a front end operational area and be capable to deal with a large team of technicians staff-s' Physically capable of performing the duties assigned.
English language fluency (written and verbal comprehension).
Able to pass a background check.
